+## [0.2.13] - 2026-06-01
+
+PATCH per the repo's pre-1.0 convention (breaking → MINOR, everything else →
+PATCH). Tags the work committed since `v0.2.12` (`dead996`…`3a683b3`): LLM
+observability via LightTrack (input/output capture + a deterministic output
+guard) hardened with a **PII redact-and-gate** policy, security headers + a
+constant-time header-only cron auth, and two pure-module unit-coverage
+additions. Every entry below is a backward-compatible **Added** or
+behavior-preserving **Changed** item — there is no `Changed (Breaking)`
+section — so the house rule lands on PATCH, not MINOR.
+
+### Added
+
+- **LLM telemetry with a PII redact-and-gate boundary** — a vendored
+  **LightTrack** client now captures LLM input/output and runs a deterministic
+  output guard (`guard()`/`GuardRules`/`trackGuard()`) across all four LLM
+  surfaces (audit, post-draft, recap, review-reply). Raw prompt/output capture
+  (which can embed customer review text and prospect-entered business data) is
+  **off by default**, gated behind `LIGHTTRACK_CAPTURE_IO`; when enabled,
+  content is PII-redacted (email / phone / SSN / card) and truncated before it
+  leaves the trust boundary. A project-scoped `tracker(source)` factory replaces
+  the hardcoded literal duplicated across the four surfaces. `redactPII` is
+  unit-tested; `.env.example` documents the LightTrack vars + capture flag.
+- **Security response headers** — `next.config.mjs` now sets HSTS,
+  `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, and
+  `Permissions-Policy` on every response; `middleware.ts` injects a per-request
+  nonce Content-Security-Policy (`script-src` nonce + `strict-dynamic` in prod,
+  `frame-ancestors 'none'` for clickjacking defense; dev loosens for HMR).
+- **Unit coverage for two pure modules** — `src/lib/format.test.ts` (ADR-0007;
+  the four formatters across negative / zero / negative-zero / NaN / rounding
+  edges, pinning the U+2212 vs ASCII-hyphen distinction) and
+  `src/lib/verticals.test.ts` (`VERTICALS` list + label completeness,
+  `normalizeVertical` defaults, `verticalNoun`). No source changes — behavior
+  pinned as-is. Suite: 274 pass / 1 pre-existing skip.
+
+### Changed
+
+- **Cron auth is header-only and constant-time** — the daily pipeline drops the
+  `?secret=` query-param path (which leaks the secret into access/proxy logs,
+  history, and `Referer`) in favor of a header compared with a SHA-256 +
+  `crypto.timingSafeEqual` constant-time check. **Operational note:** callers of
+  the cron endpoint must send the secret via the header; the query-param form no
+  longer authenticates.
+
