@@ -0,0 +1,92 @@
+# ADR-0007 — Complete `format.ts` unit coverage (finishing ADR-0001)
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-06-01
+- **Driver:** Team handoff — "stand up a test runner and write meaningful unit tests for the highest-value untested pure logic (`src/lib/format.ts`, ranking-delta / map-pack)."
+- **Author:** Solution Architect (T)
+- **Extends:** [ADR-0001](./ADR-0001-test-harness-and-pure-logic-coverage.md)
+
+## Context
+
+The seed asks the team to (a) stand up a lightweight test runner and (b) cover
+`src/lib/format.ts` and ranking-delta / map-pack logic. Grounding against the
+current tree shows the premise is **largely already satisfied** — this work was
+scoped in ADR-0001 and mostly delivered:
+
+- **Runner — DONE.** `package.json` already has
+  `"test": "node --import tsx --test \"src/**/*.test.ts\""` and `tsx` is a
+  devDependency. 19 `*.test.ts` files already run. ADR-0001 Task #1 is complete.
+- **Ranking-delta / map-pack — DONE.** The pure logic was extracted to
+  `src/lib/data/rankings.ts` (`rankDelta`, `mapPackVisibility`, `averageRank`,
+  `shareOfVoiceLeader`) and is fully edge-case tested in
+  `src/lib/data/rankings.test.ts` (climb/flat/drop, empty→0-not-NaN, clamp-100,
+  tie-resolution). `src/features/rankings/data.ts` is static fixtures only — no
+  computation to test, by design. ADR-0001 Tasks #3/#4 are effectively complete.
+- **`format.ts` — NOT DONE.** There is **no `src/lib/format.test.ts`**. The
+  four pure formatters (`formatCurrency`, `formatSignedCurrency`, `formatNumber`,
+  `formatPercent`) remain uncovered. This is ADR-0001 Task #2 + #5, unfinished.
+
+Runtime behavior re-verified on the current code (Node + tsx), to lock as the
+test contract:
+
+| Call | Result |
+|------|--------|
+| `formatCurrency(1234.5)` | `"$1,234.50"` |
+| `formatCurrency(1234.5, false)` | `"$1,235"` (0-decimal, half-expand) |
+| `formatCurrency(-1234.567)` | `"-$1,234.57"` (**ASCII hyphen** from Intl) |
+| `formatCurrency(1.005)` | `"$1.01"` (Intl half-expand) |
+| `formatCurrency(2.675)` | `"$2.68"` |
+| `formatCurrency(0)` | `"$0.00"` |
+| `formatCurrency(NaN)` | `"$NaN"` (unguarded — leaks) |
+| `formatSignedCurrency(5)` | `"+$5.00"` |
+| `formatSignedCurrency(-5)` | `"−$5.00"` (**U+2212 minus**, charCode 8722 — NOT `-`) |
+| `formatSignedCurrency(0)` | `"$0.00"` (no sign) |
+| `formatSignedCurrency(-0)` | `"$0.00"` (no sign) |
+| `formatSignedCurrency(NaN)` | `"$NaN"` |
+| `formatNumber(1234567)` | `"1,234,567"` |
+| `formatNumber(NaN)` | `"NaN"` |
+| `formatPercent(12.345)` | `"12%"` |
+| `formatPercent(12.345, 1)` | `"12.3%"` |
+| `formatPercent(-0)` | `"0%"` |
+| `formatPercent(NaN)` | `"NaN%"` |
+
+**Key trap (same as ADR-0001):** `formatSignedCurrency` emits typographic minus
+**U+2212 (`−`)** while `formatCurrency`'s own negatives use Intl's **ASCII
+hyphen (`-`)**. A test asserting the wrong glyph will spuriously fail. Both must
+be asserted with their exact characters.
+
+## Decision
+
+Write `src/lib/format.test.ts` (`node:test` + `node:assert/strict`, colocated,
+matching the house style in `src/lib/slug.test.ts`) covering all four functions
+against the verified contract above — including negative, zero, `-0`, NaN, and
+large values. **Pin current NaN behavior** (`"$NaN"`, `"NaN%"`) as a test that
+documents it; do **not** add a finite-guard or otherwise change `format.ts`.
+
+**No production defect was found** — the formatters behave consistently and the
+U+2212/ASCII split is intentional. Therefore this run is purely additive: one
+new test file, zero source changes. The NaN-leak (ADR-0001 Task #5) is a known,
+deliberately-deferred UX decision, not a newly-revealed defect; it stays OUT of
+scope here and is logged as future-work.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- **Positive:** Closes the last open item from ADR-0001. The money/percentage
+  strings users see are now regression-guarded, including the minus-glyph trap
+  that has already been called out twice.
+- **Cost:** One new test file (~30 assertions). No dependency, no source change.
+- **Explicitly OUT of scope this run** (do NOT bundle):
+  - Any edit to `src/lib/format.ts` (no NaN-guard, no glyph change).
+  - Re-testing rankings / `num.ts` — already covered.
+  - Touching the `test` script or `package.json` — runner already wired.
+  - The NaN→`"—"` finite-guard decision → deferred future-work.
+- **UNVERIFIED:** none — behavior table was executed against the live code.
+
+## Task breakdown (1 task · 2 story points)
+
+| # | Task | Scope | Pts |
+|---|------|-------|-----|
+| 1 | `format.ts` unit tests | New `src/lib/format.test.ts` covering all 4 fns to the verified contract; assert U+2212 vs ASCII hyphen, half-expand rounding, `-0`, NaN; no source changes | 2 |
+
+**Verdict:** Change fits the architecture cleanly and completes ADR-0001. 1 task,
+2 pts. Handed to Dev Clone via `architecture.analysis.completed`.
