+## Description
+Firestore saveMapPack() writes a doc per business+keyword capture and getMapPack() (firestore-store.ts) loads all docs for a business then picks the latest by captured_at in memory. Superseded captures and docs for removed keywords accumulate indefinitely, growing storage and making each read scan stale data. Delete superseded docs on save (or keep a single rolling latest doc per keyword) and bound getMapPack with a captured_at query so reads never scan orphaned history.
