+# ADR-0003 — Keyword search-volume data source (DataForSEO Keywords Data)
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-31
+- **Relates to:** [ADR-0002](./ADR-0002-parallel-pure-utility-modules.md), [ADR-0001](./ADR-0001-test-harness-and-pure-logic-coverage.md)
+- **Goal:** Local SEO Agency — ship the audit → report MVP (step: "Add ranking/keyword data source")
+
+## Context
+
+The live rank-tracking subsystem (`src/lib/serp/*`) already sources **ranking**
+data for real: `DataForSeoProvider` (`provider.ts`) fetches Google Organic —
+Live (Advanced) and the local 3-pack, parsed through zod in `parse.ts`, behind
+the `SerpProvider` boundary (`types.ts`). The deterministic `MockSerpProvider`
+backs demo/local mode.
+
+The **keyword** half of the data source is incomplete. `DataForSeoProvider.lookup()`
+returns `{ position, volume: null }` (`provider.ts:62`) — the organic SERP
+endpoint does not carry search volume. `snapshotsToKeywordRows()` (`logic.ts`)
+formats a null volume as `"—"`, so in production **every tracked keyword shows
+`volume: "—"`** while the mock path shows seeded volumes via `mockVolume()`. The
+data contract is ready: `RankingSnapshot.volume: number | null` (`types.ts`),
+`KeywordRow.volume` (`data/types.ts`), the store's `saveSnapshot(..., volume)`
+(`db.ts`), and the UI all already carry volume — only the live source is absent.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add a **monthly search-volume lookup** to the live SERP provider using
+DataForSEO's **Keywords Data → Google Ads → Search Volume (Live)** endpoint
+(`/v3/keywords_data/google_ads/search_volume/live`), mirroring the existing
+fetch-then-pure-parse split:
+
+- Pure, unit-tested request builder + zod parser added to `parse.ts`.
+- `DataForSeoProvider.lookup()` fetches volume alongside position and returns the
+  real value; a volume-fetch failure degrades to `null` (logged) and never
+  aborts the position lookup — consistent with the per-keyword error isolation
+  in `service.refreshRankings()`.
+- `MockSerpProvider` is unchanged (already returns `mockVolume`).
+
+This reuses the configured DataForSEO credentials and the
+`DATAFORSEO_SANDBOX` flag; no new provider, no new env var, no DB migration
+(the `volume` column already exists).
+
+### Considered and rejected (this run)
+
+- **Ahrefs / SEMrush keyword sync** (backlog #35) and **full SERP enrichment**
+  (backlog #36) — larger integrations, out of MVP scope. Logged as future work.
+- **A separate keyword-volume provider abstraction** — premature; volume rides
+  the same DataForSEO credential and request pattern as ranks.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- Production keyword rows show real monthly search volume instead of `"—"`.
+- One added billed endpoint per keyword refresh when DataForSEO is live (free in
+  Sandbox). Cost-capping is a separate concern (backlog #73), not this run.
+- The exact response field (`tasks[0].result[*].search_volume`) is
+  **implemented to the documented v3 API and must be verified against the free
+  Sandbox** (`DATAFORSEO_SANDBOX=1`) before trusting live figures — same posture
+  as the existing organic provider. Marked **UNVERIFIED-AGAINST-LIVE**.
+
+## Out of scope (do NOT include in this deliverable)
+
+- SerpAPI / Ahrefs / SEMrush sources; SERP feature enrichment.
+- Changes to `KeywordRow`/`RankingSnapshot` types, the UI, `service.ts` batch
+  loop, `db.ts`, or the store schema.
+- Caching, rate-limiting, or per-location budget caps.
+

