new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/adr/ADR-0004-persisted-shareable-audit-report.md
+# ADR-0004 — Persisted, shareable audit report (the "report" half of audit → report)
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-31
+- **Relates to:** [ADR-0003](./ADR-0003-keyword-search-volume-data-source.md), [ADR-0001](./ADR-0001-test-harness-and-pure-logic-coverage.md)
+- **Goal:** Local SEO Agency — ship the audit → report MVP (step: "Generate the audit report")
+
+## Context
+
+The audit funnel already produces a complete, structured scorecard. `POST /api/audit`
+(`src/app/api/audit/route.ts`) builds an `AuditReport` — `overallScore`, `grade`,
+`headline`, and five scored `AuditSection`s (`src/lib/audit.ts:55-66`) — via Gemini
+with a deterministic `templatedAudit()` fallback, so it works keyless. `AuditWizard`
+(`src/features/audit/AuditWizard.tsx`) renders it in-browser through an inline
+`ReportView`, with an email gate (`POST /api/audit-lead`) unlocking sections 2–5.
+
+The gap is the **report** half of "audit → report": the generated `AuditReport` is
+**ephemeral**. It lives only in client React state — it is never persisted and has no
+URL. `saveLead()` (`src/lib/leads/db.ts`, `Store.saveLead`, `db/schema.sql:160`) stores
+only `email + business_name + city`; **the audit content the lead was promised is
+discarded on refresh**. There is no artifact to email, share, or revisit — so the
+"10-page audit report" deliverable (BACKLOG E6, `docs/BACKLOG.md:56,71`) does not yet
+exist as a thing the prospect can receive.
+
+The persistence boundary is ready to extend: every domain writes only through the
+`Store` interface (`src/lib/db/store.ts`), with two drivers behind it
+(`pglite-store.ts` local, `firestore-store.ts` prod) chosen by `config.ts`. Adding a
+domain row is a known pattern — `saveLead` is implemented identically in both drivers
+(`pglite-store.ts:748`, `firestore-store.ts:612`).
+
+## Decision
+
+Persist each generated `AuditReport` and serve it at a **public, stable permalink**
+`/audit/r/[id]`, turning the ephemeral on-screen audit into a shareable deliverable.
+This is the minimal slice that makes "the audit report" a real artifact; it reuses the
+existing `Store` boundary and presentational components — **no new infra, no new env
+var, no LLM change.**
+
+- New `audit_reports` row carrying the full report JSON + denormalized
+  `business_name / city / vertical / overall_score / grade / created_at`, added to
+  `Store` (`saveAuditReport → id`, `getAuditReport(id)`), both drivers, and
+  `db/schema.sql` — following the `saveLead` shape exactly.
+- `POST /api/audit` persists after generation and returns `reportId` alongside the
+  audit. Persistence is **best-effort**: a store failure logs and omits `reportId`,
+  never failing the funnel (same posture as `audit-lead` capture).
+- The `ReportView` presentational subtree is extracted out of `AuditWizard` into a
+  shared `src/features/audit/ReportView.tsx` and reused by a new public,
+  server-rendered page `/audit/r/[id]` that loads the stored report (full / ungated —
+  the viewer already holds the link) and 404s when missing.
+
+### Considered and rejected (this run)
+
+- **PDF / video report** (BACKLOG E8: "PDF + HeyGen video") — heavier rendering +
+  media pipeline; the shareable HTML permalink is the MVP. Logged as future work.
+- **Gating the permalink behind auth / the email** — the report is a lead magnet;
+  a frictionless shareable link is the point. Abuse/enumeration mitigation (opaque
+  UUID is already non-sequential) is sufficient for MVP.
+- **Storing the audit on the existing `leads` row** — conflates two lifecycles
+  (a report exists before/without an email); a dedicated table keeps the funnel
+  decoupled.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- A prospect (and the captured lead) gets a real, revisitable, shareable report URL —
+  the "audit → report" pipeline reaches a deliverable instead of a transient render.
+- One new table / collection and three new `Store` methods; both drivers must stay in
+  sync (enforced by the structural `Store` interface — a missing method fails the build).
+- `ReportView` becomes a shared presentational component; the email-gate state stays in
+  `AuditWizard`, so the extraction is mechanical (props in, no behavior change).
+- Persisting the audit JSON is **UNVERIFIED-AGAINST-FIRESTORE** until run with the
+  Firestore driver — the PGlite path is covered by the integration harness (ADR-0001).
+
+## Out of scope (do NOT include in this deliverable)
+
+- PDF export, video/avatar narration, A/B report variants (BACKLOG E8).
+- Linking `reportId` into outbound cold-email / Apollo+Instantly (BACKLOG E7).
+- Per-IP rate limiting on `/api/audit` (already a standing PRODUCTION TODO).
+- Any change to audit scoring, the Gemini prompt, or `templatedAudit()`.
+- Auth-gating the permalink, report editing, or expiry/TTL.
+

