+++ b/docs/adr/ADR-0005-local-seo-audit-crawler.md
+# ADR-0005: Local-SEO audit crawler (on-page signal source)
+
+- Status: Accepted
+- Date: 2026-05-31
+- Relates to: extends ADR-0003 (live data sources), ADR-0004 (audit→report MVP). Contradicts neither.
+
+## Context
+
+The free audit (`src/lib/audit.ts` → `POST /api/audit`, `src/app/api/audit/route.ts`)
+today produces a **directional** scorecard only. Findings are generated by Gemini
+(`buildAuditPrompt`, `src/lib/audit.ts:290`) or, keyless, by `templatedAudit`
+(`src/lib/audit.ts:257`). The prompt explicitly tells the model it has **no live
+data** and must frame everything as best-practice OPPORTUNITIES — never measured
+facts. The prospect's `website` is accepted (`auditRequestSchema`,
+`src/lib/audit.ts:91`) but only **interpolated into the prompt string**
+(`src/lib/audit.ts:293`); nothing is ever fetched.
+
+The goal step "Implement the local-SEO audit crawler" is the missing data layer
+referenced in the file's own integrity note ("no live Google/SERP data yet — that
+arrives in the real data-layer direction"). On-page signals (title, meta
+description, H1, mobile viewport, LocalBusiness JSON-LD, NAP presence, HTTPS) are
+the one class of audit input that can be **directly observed** from the public
+site — so they can be cited as real measurements without violating the
+no-fabrication rule that still governs GBP / reviews / rankings.
+
+The established pattern for an external data source is `src/lib/serp/`: a **pure,
+unit-tested request-builder + parser** (`parse.ts`, no `server-only`, no `fetch`,
+no deps beyond zod) and a thin **`server-only` provider** that only does the
+`fetch` and calls the pure layer (`provider.ts`). Per-item failures degrade
+gracefully (null/logged), never aborting the batch. No HTML-parsing dependency
+(cheerio/jsdom) is installed, and the SERP parser shows regex/string extraction
+is the house style.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add an audit crawler as a new `src/lib/audit/` module pair that mirrors the SERP
+fetch-then-parse split, **with zero new dependencies**:
+
+- `src/lib/audit/crawl.ts` — **pure**: `parseSiteSignals(html, finalUrl)` extracts
+  on-page signals via regex into a single `SiteSignals` type; `unreachableSignals(url)`
+  is the fallback shape. No `fetch`, no `server-only` → fully unit-testable.
+- `src/lib/audit/crawler.ts` — **`server-only`**: `crawlSite(url)` normalizes the
+  URL, fetches with a timeout + body cap, and returns `SiteSignals`. **Never throws** —
+  any failure returns `unreachableSignals` (same posture as the unmetered funnel).
+
+Wire the signals into the **LLM path only**: `buildAuditPrompt(req, signals?)`
+appends an "observed on-page signals" block (the single sanctioned real-measurement
+exception) and `route.ts` calls `crawlSite(body.website)` before building the
+prompt when a website is supplied. The keyless `templatedAudit` path stays
+zero-network and unchanged.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- The Gemini audit can ground its on-page findings (title/meta/schema/mobile/HTTPS/NAP)
+  in real, crawled facts; GBP/reviews/citations/competitors remain directional.
+- New surface is fully testable offline (pure parser) and degrades to today's
+  behavior when the site is unreachable or no website is given.
+- No new npm dependency; HTML parsed by regex like `serp/parse.ts`.
+
+### Explicitly OUT of scope this run (logged as future work, not bundled here)
+
+- Per-IP rate limiting / SSRF hardening on the now-outbound-fetching public route
+  (standing PRODUCTION TODO in `route.ts`).
+- Grounding the **template** path, or changing scoring math / `templatedAudit`
+  structure / `parseAuditResponse`.
+- Persisting crawl results (ADR-0004 report persistence is separate).
+- Robots.txt handling, multi-page crawl, screenshot/Lighthouse/PageSpeed signals,
+  cheerio/jsdom adoption.
+- UI changes (`AuditWizard.tsx`) and DB schema changes.
+
+### Considered and rejected
+
+- **Add cheerio/jsdom for parsing** — rejected: a dependency for a handful of
+  regex extractions, against the `serp/parse.ts` house style.
+- **Crawl inside `templatedAudit` (keyless path)** — rejected: that path is the
+  zero-network CI/keyless guarantee; adding a fetch there breaks it.
+- **Call Google PageSpeed/Lighthouse APIs** — rejected for MVP: adds a credentialed
+  external dependency; raw on-page HTML covers the audit's five sections' on-page needs.
+

