+# ADR-0006: Audit report export (pure HTML builder + print-to-PDF)
+
+- Status: Accepted
+- Date: 2026-05-31
+- Mode: TEAM HANDOFF (T: Solution Architect scopes → Dev Clone implements)
+- Goal: Local SEO Agency — ship the audit → report MVP / step "Wire report export"
+- Relates to: ADR-0004 (persisted shareable report — NOT yet implemented), ADR-0001 (node:test pure-logic harness), ADR-0002 (parallel pure-utility modules)
+
+## Context
+
+The free-audit funnel already GENERATES a complete `AuditReport`
+(`businessName / city / vertical / overallScore / grade / headline /
+sections[]`, defined `src/lib/audit.ts:60-69`) via `POST /api/audit`, and
+`src/features/audit/AuditWizard.tsx` renders it on the `"result"` step
+(`AuditWizard.tsx:358-379`, sub-components `ReportHeader` @135 and `SectionCard`
+@181). The report lives ONLY in client React state
+(`ReportState = {status:"ok"; report}`, `AuditWizard.tsx:28-32, 325`): a
+prospect cannot take it with them. The result step's only action today is
+"Run another audit" (`AuditWizard.tsx:367-376`). The audit → report MVP's
+"report" deliverable is therefore not yet portable.
+
+ADR-0004 (persistence + `/audit/r/[id]` permalink + shared `ReportView`) is
+written but NOT implemented — no report route, no shared component, no DB
+columns exist. So "Wire report export" must work off what renders TODAY, with
+no dependency on persistence.
+
+Harness constraints that shape the decision (verified, not assumed):
+- Test runner is **`node:test` via tsx**, glob `src/**/*.test.ts`
+  (`package.json` `test` script). There is **no Vitest, no jsdom, no
+  @testing-library/react** — only `.test.ts` pure-logic tests
+  (pattern: `src/lib/audit.test.ts`). React component DOM tests are NOT
+  supported by the harness.
+- `globals.css` has **no `@media print` rule** today; the page renders a heavy
+  fixed cartograph background (`body::before/::after`) that must not bleed into
+  a printout.
+- Button primitives are `.btn-ink` / `.btn-ghost` / `.btn-signal` (no CSS deps).
+- Standing repo posture: **zero new npm dependencies** for this class of feature
+  (ADR-0005).
+
+## Decision
+
+Export = **generate a self-contained, standalone HTML document from the
+`AuditReport` and open it in a new tab for the user to Save-as-PDF / print.**
+
+Split per ADR-0002 (pure module + thin caller):
+1. A **pure, dependency-free builder** `buildReportHtml(report: AuditReport):
+   string` in a new `src/features/audit/reportExport.ts` — no React/Next/DOM
+   imports — returning a complete `<!doctype html>…</html>` string with inlined
+   CSS (brand colors as literal hex, print-friendly, no external assets). This
+   is unit-testable under the existing `node:test` harness.
+2. A **thin client handler** in `AuditWizard.tsx` wired to a new "Export PDF"
+   button on the result step: `window.open()` a blank tab, write the built HTML,
+   call `print()`. No new dependency, no server route, no schema change.
+
+Chosen over print-CSS-on-the-live-page because (a) the live page's fixed
+cartograph background + nav chrome fight the printout, and (b) a pure HTML
+builder is testable in THIS harness whereas a `window.print()`-on-page handler
+is not. The builder also becomes the reusable seam for ADR-0004's future
+permalink/PDF work.
+
+Considered & rejected: server-side PDF (puppeteer / @react-pdf/renderer) — heavy
+dep + render route, violates zero-dep posture; HeyGen video / PDF media pipeline
+(BACKLOG E8) — far out of a single export step; print-only CSS on live page —
+not unit-testable here, background bleed.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- Prospects get a clean, portable PDF of their audit straight from the result
+  screen — the MVP's "report" half becomes a real deliverable with zero backend
+  work.
+- New pure module is covered by the existing `node:test` runner (no harness
+  change). Print fidelity relies on the browser engine (acceptable for MVP).
+- When ADR-0004's permalink + shared `ReportView` land, `buildReportHtml` is
+  reused unchanged for server/download paths.
+
+### Explicitly OUT of scope this run (do NOT touch)
+- Report persistence, `/audit/r/[id]` permalink, shared `ReportView` extraction
+  (ADR-0004 — separate step).
+- Crawler / on-page signals (ADR-0005).
+- Server-side PDF generation; ANY new npm dependency; adding Vitest/jsdom/RTL.
+- HeyGen video, A/B report variants, PDF media pipeline (BACKLOG E8).
+- Cold-email reportId wiring (BACKLOG E7); per-IP rate limiting on `/api/audit`.
+- `src/lib/audit.ts`, `/api/audit/route.ts`, the Store / DB layer.
+

